### [Numbers Chapter 16](../../../bib/kjv/num016.htm#001.md)

[Numbers 16:10](../../../bib/kjv/num016.htm#010.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_010">num 16:10</span></span>

Seek ye the priesthood also

The "gainsaying of Korah" was intrusion into the priest's office ("no
man taketh this honour unto himself,") ([Heb
5:4](../../../bib/kjv/heb005.htm#004).md). It was an attempt to create a
priestly order without the divine authority ([Heb
5:10](../../../bib/kjv/heb005.htm#010).md). The modern analogue is
Nicolaitanism ([Rev 2:6](../../../bib/kjv/rev002.htm#006).md); ([Rev
2:15](../../../bib/kjv/rev002.htm#015).md) the division of an equal
brotherhood ([Mat 23:8](../../../bib/kjv/mat023.htm#008).md) into "clergy"
and "laity"; a vastly different thing from the due recognition of
ministry-gifts; ([Co1 12:4-31](../../../bib/kjv/co1012.htm#004).md); ([Eph
4:8](../../../bib/kjv/eph004.htm#008).md); ([Eph
4:11](../../../bib/kjv/eph004.htm#011).md); ([Eph
4:12](../../../bib/kjv/eph004.htm#012).md) or of elders and deacons; ([Ti1
3:1-13](../../../bib/kjv/ti1003.htm#001).md); ([Tit
1:5-9](../../../bib/kjv/tit001.htm#005).md).

